FORMER SABC and North West FM presenter Chris Matshaba has died. The DJ and businessman left SABC’s Motsweding FM many times only to return by popular demand. In 2013 he left Motsweding for good and joined North West FM in Rustenburg. He continued pursuing business interests and finally left North West FM to focus on his businesses. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>North West FM station manager David Mabusela said Chris was not only a close friend and former colleague, but a business partner too. “We owned Motswana Investments together and had many plans.“Chris was not only good behind the microphone, but also understood the media business,” said David. “On behalf of the station and his former colleagues, we are passing our condolences to his wife Tsholo, kids and the rest of the family.” He got married to Tsholo Monedi, popularly known as Meme on Muvhango, in 2014. The details of his death are still unclear as the SunTeam was unable to reach his family.According to Facebook posts and his niece Sheila Matshaba’s Twitter account, he died in hospital. Chris was originally from Ramokokastad near Rustenburg.He died at 2pm on Saturday, and by yesterday messages of condolence were pouring in from his fans. A friend and former radio colleague, Kabelo Mosito, said he was saddened by the loss. “Chris was a jolly person who was loved by everyone. “He used to go the extra mile to help others. “We started together on Radio Turf, a campus radio station, and ended up on Motsweding,” said Mosito. Family spokesman Kabelo said the details of the memorial service will be communicated in due course.The funeral service will take place in Ramokokastad this coming Saturday.